00:12:27.520 --> 00:12:31.080
The National Book Festival is
not only a celebration of books

00:12:31.080 --> 00:12:35.300
and reading, but also
of literacy itself.

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:39.070
Life, in these demanding times,
can be very difficult for those

00:12:39.070 --> 00:12:42.320
who have never learned to
read, and unfortunately,

00:12:42.320 --> 00:12:44.910
there are too many
people in that number,

00:12:44.910 --> 00:12:47.620
in this country, and
around the world.

00:12:47.620 --> 00:12:53.350
The latest estimate, is that 65
percent of adults in the world,

00:12:53.350 --> 00:12:56.240
are functionally illiterate.

00:12:56.240 --> 00:13:00.290
At the Library, it is an
important part of our mission

00:13:00.290 --> 00:13:05.570
to comet illiteracy, and
promote a culture of reading,

00:13:05.570 --> 00:13:08.690
and one of the most generous
supporters of American Culture,

00:13:08.690 --> 00:13:14.230
History, and the Arts in this
country is Mr. David Rubenstein,

00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:18.830
Co-Chair of the National Book
Festival, and is primary donor.

00:13:18.830 --> 00:13:22.890
His patriotic philanthropy can
be seen all across Washington,

00:13:22.890 --> 00:13:26.790
at the Kennedy Center, the National
Zoo, the Washington Monument,

00:13:26.790 --> 00:13:28.930
and at the new National Museum

00:13:28.930 --> 00:13:31.410
of African American
History and Culture.

00:13:31.410 --> 00:13:37.420
But his work can also be seen all
across the country, and the world.

00:13:37.420 --> 00:13:41.910
He is a tireless promoter of
literacy, and he believes in books,

00:13:41.910 --> 00:13:46.440 position:56%
libraries, and the opportunity, and
success that are [inaudible] linked,

00:13:46.440 --> 00:13:51.750
and I trust they are for
all of us here tonight.

00:13:51.750 --> 00:13:55.860
His dedication to increasing
literacy across the world,

00:13:55.860 --> 00:13:58.640
let to his creation and
support of the Library

00:13:58.640 --> 00:14:01.540
of Congress Literacy Awards.

